Privacy Policy for Email Cleanup Assistant

Last updated: 18 May, 2025

Email Cleanup Assistant is a Chrome extension developed by The Thrive Cart. We respect your privacy and are committed to protecting your data. This policy explains how our extension accesses, uses, and protects your information.

1. Data Collection
This extension only requests access to your Gmail inbox metadata through the scope:

https://www.googleapis.com/auth/gmail.readonly

We do not collect, store, or transmit any personal data to any external server. All data is accessed temporarily to help you identify promotional, social, or unread emails within the browser.

2. Use of Permissions
OAuth2 Authentication: Used only to securely authenticate your Gmail account.

Gmail Readonly Scope: Allows us to read metadata (like subject lines and labels) for cleanup suggestions. We never modify, delete, or send emails.

Identity: Needed to initiate secure OAuth login.

3. No Third-Party Sharing
Your Gmail data is never shared with third-party services or advertisers.

4. Data Retention
We do not store any of your email data. The extension runs entirely in your browser session.

5. User Control
You may revoke the extensionâ€™s access at any time via your Google account: Google Permissions

6. Contact
For questions, contact: thethrivecart.ltd@gmail.com
